The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, May 16, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Sunday, May 16, 2004				 																Design Sense				 																																	Drop in at 20X30, an inaugural exhibition of decorative posters by Shuvaprasanna, Aditya Basak, Jogen Chowdhury and others, at the opening of Arts amp; Ideas Designshop at Swabhumi, at 6 pm. Worry not about making the right design decisions. The Urban Zone shop has a solution for every design problem  be it art, photography or publishing. A perfect mix of hi-tech and artistry. Southern Delight				 																																	Dont miss the special screening of Dum Dum Dum, courtesy Institute of Mass Communication Film and Television Studies, at Priya, at 9.15 am. Director Azagam Perumals Tamil debut stars Madhavan and Jyothika in a comic drama produced by Mani Rathnam. Its the same boy-meets-girl story, except that here the pair vows, against the parents wishes, not to fall in love! Watch out for camerawork and song picturisation. Footwork Feat				 																																	The Gaudia Nritya workshop from 3 pm to 6 pm, at Nehru Childrens Museum will keep your kids engaged in perfecting their footwork, while the rest of the family can have a quiet evening out. 
